reviews.reviewText: A mi hijo le gustó mucho

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on June 2, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Perfect Gift For My 6 Year Old!
reviews.reviewText: Bought this for my 6 year old around Christmas time and he absolutely loved it. It was a little too much for him specifically to sit and do himself at first but with me standing by to give him a hand or just to point him in the right direction, he started picking up on it fairly quickly. It was such a mom-mazing moment to watch as he progressively learned to make these Suttle connections in his head to start visually being able to picture how something is supposed to look and making it come to life in front of his eyes. What an awesome product!!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on May 8, 2021
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Great price, a lot like Legos, but fragile!
reviews.reviewText: My sons enjoyed putting this together and were able to figure out the directions on their own. The only downside is it's really hard to play with once it's built because it breaks easily. The parts kept falling off when they played with it. Once it's built it's more for display.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 28, 2020
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Fun building kit
reviews.reviewText: This toy was honestly better than I expected. My four year old was a tad too young to follow the directions on his own, but It ended up being a really fun family activity. There are several planes and vehicles to build on their own - and then can be combined altogether to build a giant transformer like robot.I’m not sure we’ll make it to that point, but it’s fun to break up the building of the vehicles into multiple days. It’s nice that it doesn’t lose its luster after day one. I’ll definitely be purchasing this again in the future as a holiday or birthday gift. 👍🏼

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 29, 2023
reviews.reviewText: I bought this as a Christmas gift for a 7-year-old boy. He is very into lego, so this was a hit initially. But it quickly became apparent that it was too delicate. It kept falling apart as he was building it. Lots of parts of the robot are attached by only one or two lego units. He eventually finished it, but he cannot play with it because as soon as he tries moving it an arm will break off. This is only suitable for display, which isn't what a 7-year-old wants.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 9, 2022
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Awesome and Lego compatible!
reviews.reviewText: I ordered these for my 7 year old son for Christmas. He is able to follow the instructions and build the basic models completely by himself, which he is proud of. I didn’t know they were Lego compatible when I got them, which was an added bonus. Very impressed so far!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 5, 2022
reviews.reviewText: This set is a great building set! It has a lot of little pieces, so we build in increments. Resembles Disney princess movie. Good quality. Comparable to Lego’s.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 14, 2022
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Love building and arranging
reviews.reviewText: My kids absolutely love building with these. It helps them to be so imaginative and really be hands on.

My recent adventure with the MOONTOY Princess Castle STEM Blocks was enchanting and magical. Priced at $25.99 less $2.00 coupon, this set, enclosed in a beautiful giftable box, mirrors LEGO pieces and offers excellent value with its substantial piece count. However, it's essential to note that the abundance of pieces may not be suitable for younger kids or those lacking patience for intricate block play. The MOONTOY Princess Castle, themed as the "Blue Princess Castle," lives up to its promise of a joyful childhood dreamscape, featuring 492 easy-to-assemble pieces with step-by-step instructions and pretty stickers for enhanced creativity. Not only does it inspire imaginative play, but it also serves as a valuable tool for STEM education, and the inclusion of safety certifications and a warranty reflects MOONTOY's commitment to excellent service. Overall, the Princess Castle STEM Blocks offer a delightful journey into creativity and education, making it a recommended and special experience for builders of all ages.
